      <title>Pets in PVP</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12090#M12090</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;My 70 pet (necromancer) is pretty pitiful against players that attack me (mostly level 70s).  He's supposed to be my melee DPS, but he generally hits for 15-20 points when he hits PVP.  He hits for 150-200 and backstabs for more at times against mobs when he's buffed.  Nothing but a distraction PVP though.  Against a caster I guess he might be a benefit in interrupting them, but I almost never get ganked by casters.  It's generally monks, rogues, sks, warriors.  They could really care less if my pet's beating on their back for 15 points while they're trying to beat me down.  So, my question is this.  Is there something I should be doing to make him more effective PVP?  Should I be dire charming some undead mob instead of using the summoned pet, and then using my suspend AA to hang onto him?  Is he useless without toys?  Hasted and buffed, he does well against mobs even without toys, so I don't usually bother seeking them out.  Any tips would be appreciated.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
