      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&amp;message.id=12262#M12262</link>
      <description>1) Ask yourself 'Can my pet tank a level 70-75 mob by itself?'&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Yes, Pets do suck in PVP and probably always will from this point on. Back in the day pets used to be more beneficial and damaging&amp;nbsp; but this resulted in the 'melee kite' where a necro/mage would sic a pet on a melee and then run around while the pet ate away at their health. If the melee stopped to try and kill the pet then the necro/mage would stop and start nuking the melee. End Result: The only way to beat a necro/mage back in the day was to get them snared/rooted and/or force them to zone (back before pets living through zoning bit was introduced). Ofcourse epic mage pets used to rip up entire groups... Pets were effectively a walking DOT so they were treated as such and given a 66% damage nerf on them in PVP.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
